// tools/manifest.json — MCP tool registry.
//
// JSONC RULES (enforced by the inline shim in 7 consumers; see
// mastra/server.js:15-19 for the canonical example):
//   - Only full-line `//` comments are allowed; NO inline `// ...` after code.
//   - No trailing commas.
//   - Anything else (block comments, unquoted keys, etc.) will fail the parse.
//
// WHY THE PATH REWRITE: entries use the CANONICAL name "tools/X-tool.js"
// (stable, hand-curated). At server startup, mastra/server.js:26-27 rewrites
// each path to "../tools/handlers/X-tool.js" (the "legacy MCP wrapper"
// implementation). This keeps the registry stable while allowing file moves
// between tools/, tools/handlers/, and future mastra/tools/.
//
// pathFields (R3 / Plan 5-Lite Phase 1): declares which arg names carry WRITE
// path values that the R2 gate must ownership-check. Empty array [] means
// "this tool takes no write-path args" → the gate short-circuits to allow.
// Most legacy tools write to FIXED internal paths (meta-state.jsonl, records/**)
// resolved from non-path args (ids, structured data) → they declare [].
// validateToolManifest throws at boot if any entry is missing pathFields.
//
// Keep entries in sync with dynamicallyLoaded in .fallowrc.json (which
// fallow needs to credit dynamic imports).
[
  { "file": "tools/gate-tool.js", "export": "gateCheckTool", "pathFields": [] },
  { "file": "tools/gate-override-tool.js", "export": "gateOverrideTool", "pathFields": [] },
